						<summary>

						<p>Impression received from Dr. G.S. Dixit, Karnataka University, Dharwar [Findspot-Kolhapur].</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Nūrmaḍi Chakravartti Trailōkyamalla [Sōmēśvara IV] 12th century A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>The record is broken and damaged. It belongs to the reign period of Chālukya Nūrmaḍi Trailōkyamalla. It seems to register a gift of land to the god Sankēśvaradēva. It refers to Bijjala and <hi rend="italic">mahājanās</hi> of an <hi rend="italic">agrahāra</hi> [name lost]. The record gives the genealogy of the king and the general Kāḷidāsa.</p>						

						<p>Regarding the date only Śivarātri 14 Monday is available. It is in the 12th century A.D. characters.</p>						

						</summary>
